The paper is about object detection using a fully convolutional neural network (FCN) and incorporates landmark localization during multi-task learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses optimization and accuracy, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions benchmark datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
